1
00:03:09,289 --> 00:03:11,553
Such a tragedy.

2
00:03:11,658 --> 00:03:13,319
A whole family.

3
00:03:13,426 --> 00:03:16,395
Who told them to ride a bicycle
50 feet in the air?

4
00:03:16,496 --> 00:03:17,724
And they're from Roma.

5
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:19,695
They should
have been buried in Roma.

6
00:03:19,799 --> 00:03:21,027
Just because they die here

7
00:03:21,134 --> 00:03:23,534
doesn't give them the right
to clutter up our cemetery.

8
00:04:42,015 --> 00:04:43,880
<i>- Buon Giorno!
- Buon Giorno!</i>

9
00:05:09,275 --> 00:05:11,175
How long has the doctor
been here?

10
00:05:11,277 --> 00:05:12,676
About 20 minutes.

11
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:14,303
I don't think it's serious.

12
00:05:19,285 --> 00:05:20,684
That poor man.

13
00:05:20,787 --> 00:05:23,688
He doesn't know whether to
pray for her to get better or worse.

14
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:26,350
You don't pray for someone
to get worse.

15
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:28,359
God doesn't like that.

16
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:30,861
So you know what God
likes and doesn't like?

17
00:05:30,963 --> 00:05:32,988
He doesn't like me
to win at cards.

18
00:05:33,099 --> 00:05:34,066
Hah hah hah!

19
00:05:35,301 --> 00:05:37,030
What happened?
What's wrong?

20
00:05:37,136 --> 00:05:38,364
She was coughing.

21
00:05:38,471 --> 00:05:39,938
It's nothing, Marcello.

22
00:05:40,039 --> 00:05:41,870
Cecilia shouldn't have
bothered the doctor.

23
00:05:41,974 --> 00:05:43,339
So why did you?

24
00:05:43,443 --> 00:05:44,876
She's my sister.

25
00:05:44,977 --> 00:05:47,207
I have a right to call
when you're not here, as usual.

26
00:05:47,313 --> 00:05:48,678
What do you mean, "as usual"?

27
00:05:48,781 --> 00:05:50,544
Well, who's been
waiting tables all day?

28
00:05:50,650 --> 00:05:53,278
I don't know, but there are
four men downstairs who need coffee.

29
00:05:53,386 --> 00:05:55,854
Well, let them get their own.
I don't get paid for this, you know.

30
00:06:00,159 --> 00:06:02,821
Marcello, was that necessary?

31
00:06:02,929 --> 00:06:06,421
I'm sorry, but I see the doctor's car
and I get palpitations.

32
00:06:07,533 --> 00:06:10,502
Take the poor man downstairs
and give him a drink.

33
00:06:10,603 --> 00:06:13,538
He was up all night
at the Borglione house.

34
00:06:13,639 --> 00:06:15,368
She had twins.

35
00:06:15,475 --> 00:06:17,340
Healthy? No complications?

36
00:06:17,443 --> 00:06:18,842
They're all fine. Relax.

37
00:06:20,079 --> 00:06:21,239
How was the funeral?

38
00:06:21,347 --> 00:06:22,837
It was a funeral...

39
00:06:22,949 --> 00:06:26,544
a lot of tears, a lot of sighs,
and into the ground.

40
00:06:26,652 --> 00:06:29,348
Now only three more graves left.

41
00:06:29,455 --> 00:06:32,356
And Pavone and Aprea
are heading for two of them.

42
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:34,289
How is Pavone?
Any improvement?

43
00:06:34,394 --> 00:06:36,259
There is nothing I can do for him.

44
00:06:36,362 --> 00:06:37,852
You could call a specialist.

45
00:06:37,964 --> 00:06:40,865
The only specialist he needs
is a stone mason.

46
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:42,025
What about Aprea?

47
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:43,534
Does he need blood?
I'll give him blood.

48
00:06:43,636 --> 00:06:44,898
No, no, no, no, Marcello.

49
00:06:45,004 --> 00:06:48,030
You can't give any more blood.
You gave blood yesterday.

50
00:06:48,141 --> 00:06:50,439
You can't keep everyone
in the whole town alive.

51
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:52,568
I can try.

52
00:06:58,985 --> 00:07:00,577
Roseanna's right.

53
00:07:00,686 --> 00:07:02,210
You can't play God.

54
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:05,950
Anyone in Trevento could
drop dead at any minute...

55
00:07:06,058 --> 00:07:07,491
heart attack,

56
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:09,993
lungs collapsing,
kidney failure,

57
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:12,326
brain tumor,
blood poisoning...

58
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:14,195
Then you're not doing your job!

59
00:07:21,307 --> 00:07:22,706
What's the matter?

60
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:24,640
It's on the high end
of normal.

61
00:07:24,744 --> 00:07:26,006
That good?

62
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,847
It means you're stressed.

63
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:32,110
I'll give you some pills.

64
00:07:32,218 --> 00:07:35,551
You're a nice man, Sergio.
Have a Fernet-Branca.

65
00:07:35,655 --> 00:07:37,350
I'd rather get paid.

66
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:40,017
Why don't people
pay their doctor?

67
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:42,526
Is it because
I don't leave anything behind?

68
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:44,493
You'd pay me if I delivered
tomatoes or veal chops.

69
00:07:44,597 --> 00:07:47,031
People don't pay you
because they have no money

70
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:48,327
and they think you have a lot.

71
00:07:48,434 --> 00:07:50,368
A gynecologist in Roma
has a lot.

72
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,199
A plastic surgeon in Milan.

73
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:55,797
I don't have enough to take my wife
to the sea for a few days...

74
00:07:55,908 --> 00:07:58,240
...so you know where we're going?
- Where?

75
00:07:58,344 --> 00:07:59,868
The attic of our house.

76
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:02,641
There's a window
that faces the sea.

77
00:08:02,748 --> 00:08:03,976
It's 30 kilometers away,

78
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:06,745
but we are going to pray
for a very high tide.

79
00:08:06,853 --> 00:08:08,320
Sergio, when you leave,

80
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:10,389
go out the back
and take a couple of eggs.

81
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,958
You owe me 10,000 eggs.

82
00:08:13,059 --> 00:08:16,256
Then take the chicken
and bring it back when we're even.

83
00:09:04,143 --> 00:09:06,634
<i>Corpus Cristo.</i>

84
00:09:22,929 --> 00:09:24,829
- Roseanna.
- Father.

85
00:09:24,931 --> 00:09:26,159
How are you doing?

86
00:09:26,265 --> 00:09:28,165
We're still discussing that with God.

87
00:09:28,267 --> 00:09:30,565
And I'm sure He's listening.

88
00:09:33,306 --> 00:09:34,500
<i>Ciao.</i>

89
00:09:34,607 --> 00:09:37,838
Eh, Cecilia, do you
remember me? Antonio.

90
00:09:37,944 --> 00:09:39,002
I know who you are.

91
00:09:39,111 --> 00:09:40,339
I thought you might have forgotten.

92
00:09:40,446 --> 00:09:42,346
I've been away a long time.

93
00:09:42,448 --> 00:09:44,245
- Law school, wasn't it?
- Yes.

94
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:46,716
Stop! Stop! Stop!

95
00:09:46,819 --> 00:09:48,343
What is Marcello doing?

96
00:09:48,454 --> 00:09:50,922
My sister is very ill.

97
00:09:51,023 --> 00:09:52,183
She has a bad heart,

98
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:54,020
and her one wish is to be buried
in the cemetery,

99
00:09:54,126 --> 00:09:55,354
and there's only
a few graves left.

100
00:09:55,461 --> 00:09:57,088
And Marcello doesn't want
anyone else to die.

101
00:09:57,196 --> 00:09:58,857
He doesn't want any accidents.

102
00:09:58,965 --> 00:10:00,523
Helmet! Helmet!

103
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:04,069
Helmet, you guys!
You guys could get killed!

104
00:10:04,837 --> 00:10:05,826
That is very moving.

105
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:08,668
It's absurd, and it's
all your uncle's fault.

106
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:09,934
My uncle?

107
00:10:10,042 --> 00:10:12,374
Well, you know he owns the land
next to the cemetery,

108
00:10:12,478 --> 00:10:14,207
and the church has offered
to buy, and he won't sell.

109
00:10:14,313 --> 00:10:15,371
Not even half an acre.

110
00:10:15,481 --> 00:10:17,642
This... this is the first
I've heard of it.

111
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,911
<i>Scusi. Scusi. I think I'd like
to go home now, eh?</i>

112
00:10:20,019 --> 00:10:21,043
Of course.

113
00:10:21,153 --> 00:10:22,120
<i>Buon Giorno.</i>

114
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:24,957
Antonio.

115
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:32,019
Stop it! Stop it!

116
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:35,700
Seatbelt! Seatbelt!

117
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:39,259
Seatbelt!
Ha ha ha ha! Seatbelt!

118
00:11:06,332 --> 00:11:07,697
<i>Buon Giorno!</i>

119
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,700
Nice of you to join us.

120
00:11:09,802 --> 00:11:11,030
What do you mean by that?

121
00:11:11,137 --> 00:11:13,367
We need another waiter
more than we need a traffic cop.

122
00:11:13,472 --> 00:11:16,066
Cecilia, you should remember
you're a guest in my house.

123
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:17,233
Oh, really?

124
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:19,868
I thought I was my sister's nurse
and unpaid waitress.

125
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:21,537
I didn't realize I was a guest.

126
00:11:21,647 --> 00:11:23,239
Perhaps tomorrow
you bring me breakfast in bed

127
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:24,976
with fresh orange juice.

128
00:11:26,085 --> 00:11:29,384
Hey, hey, why are you
always fighting with Cecilia?

129
00:11:29,488 --> 00:11:30,716
She's family.

130
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:32,723
I don't want her to feel like family.

131
00:11:32,825 --> 00:11:35,555
I want her to feel like a guest.
Like then I can ask her to leave.

132
00:11:35,661 --> 00:11:38,926
Marcello! She gave up
her life in Rome to look after me.

133
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:41,557
I can look after you.

134
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:45,569
When did she last see a movie
or go out on a date, eh?

135
00:11:45,671 --> 00:11:48,071
She's such a princess.
She says to me once,

136
00:11:48,174 --> 00:11:51,405
"I don't want to be with a man
with dirt under his nails,"

137
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:54,411
which rules out almost
every man in this province.

138
00:11:54,513 --> 00:11:55,912
Antonio has beautiful hands,

139
00:11:56,015 --> 00:11:58,916
and he was making sheep's eyes
at her at church this morning.

140
00:11:59,018 --> 00:12:01,509
Typical of your sister
to impress a Capestro.

141
00:12:03,789 --> 00:12:06,349
- Too much oregano.
- She's a beautiful woman.

142
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:08,359
No. You are a beautiful woman.

143
00:12:08,461 --> 00:12:11,862
You walk into a room,
and you take all the light, mmm.

144
00:12:12,965 --> 00:12:15,695
Cecilia, she has a certain, uh...

145
00:12:15,801 --> 00:12:18,770
you know,
sexy thing going for her.

146
00:12:18,871 --> 00:12:20,498
Sexy?

147
00:12:20,606 --> 00:12:22,233
She has, uh...

148
00:12:22,341 --> 00:12:24,332
she has certain assets,

149
00:12:24,443 --> 00:12:26,843
but what she's got,
she makes the men too aware of.

150
00:12:26,946 --> 00:12:30,677
I didn't realize you were aware
of my sister's assets.

151
00:12:30,783 --> 00:12:32,842
- I'm not.
- You just said you were.

152
00:12:32,952 --> 00:12:34,544
How did this start?

153
00:12:34,653 --> 00:12:35,881
You just said
you thought she was sexy.

154
00:12:35,988 --> 00:12:37,387
L... I didn't.

155
00:12:37,490 --> 00:12:40,323
I meant other men do.
Some men, not me.

156
00:13:00,179 --> 00:13:01,407
So...

157
00:13:01,514 --> 00:13:03,448
did you talk to Capestro again?

158
00:13:03,549 --> 00:13:06,814
I've raised the offer...
50 million lire.

159
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:09,854
50 million lire? That is twice
what the land is worth.

160
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:11,047
Marcello!

161
00:13:11,157 --> 00:13:12,249
<i>- More vino.
- No more vino!</i>

162
00:13:12,358 --> 00:13:15,589
<i>- What do you mean, no more vino?
- You have a long drive home!</i>

163
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:20,257
You smoke too much.

164
00:13:20,366 --> 00:13:21,833
Marcello!

165
00:13:21,934 --> 00:13:23,902
So, can you go higher?

166
00:13:24,003 --> 00:13:26,369
There is no more money.

167
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:29,202
We'll buy Emilio Fela's land
for a new cemetery.

168
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:31,003
It's up in the hills above the town.

169
00:13:31,110 --> 00:13:34,307
But it's Roseanna's dying wish.

170
00:13:34,413 --> 00:13:37,007
I know. I know.

171
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:42,749
I'm coming.

172
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:55,391
What are you doing?

173
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:57,731
I was just thinking
I'll never wear this again.

174
00:13:57,837 --> 00:13:59,896
I wonder how much
I could get for it.

175
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:02,337
I won't hear of it.
It's a family treasure.

176
00:14:02,441 --> 00:14:03,840
It belonged to your grandmother.

177
00:14:03,943 --> 00:14:05,171
I'll sell a kidney.

178
00:14:05,277 --> 00:14:08,007
It's only been
in the family 43 years.

179
00:14:11,116 --> 00:14:14,381
In America, a person
can reserve a grave in advance.

180
00:14:14,486 --> 00:14:16,351
Doesn't surprise me.

181
00:14:16,455 --> 00:14:20,016
In America, you can do everything
without getting out of your car.

182
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:22,025
I always wanted to see New York.

183
00:14:22,127 --> 00:14:24,357
I always promised to take you there.

184
00:14:24,463 --> 00:14:26,021
And I will.

185
00:14:27,299 --> 00:14:29,529
- First class?
- Of course first class.

186
00:14:29,635 --> 00:14:31,865
We will need three seats...

187
00:14:31,971 --> 00:14:34,371
one for you,
and two for my coffin.

188
00:14:34,473 --> 00:14:35,872
We don't talk like that.

189
00:14:35,975 --> 00:14:38,705
As long as there is life,
there are dreams.

190
00:14:38,811 --> 00:14:41,871
All right. After New York,
we go to Paris.

191
00:14:41,981 --> 00:14:43,505
It's full of French people.

192
00:14:43,616 --> 00:14:45,516
Why put ourselves through that?

193
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:50,549
No, but really, what do you think
I could get for this, eh? Huh?

194
00:14:50,656 --> 00:14:54,854
I don't know, eh, but for
100,000 lire, I'll give you a kiss.

195
00:14:56,161 --> 00:14:58,186
What do you have for 200,000?

196
00:15:03,769 --> 00:15:05,327
Eh, what's wrong?

197
00:15:05,437 --> 00:15:07,496
Cecilia,
she can hear everything.

198
00:15:07,606 --> 00:15:10,336
It's another reason
I hate guests in the house.

199
00:15:10,442 --> 00:15:12,342
Who cares?
Don't think about it.

200
00:15:12,444 --> 00:15:16,346
I can't. A moment ago
I was like a rod, and now...

201
00:15:29,962 --> 00:15:32,522
Marcello, Marcello, slow down.
Slow down, eh?

202
00:15:32,631 --> 00:15:35,031
It's the music.
Change the station.

203
00:15:35,134 --> 00:15:38,069
The station...
the station...

204
00:16:09,368 --> 00:16:11,268
Good morning, Gianna.
How is he?

205
00:16:16,575 --> 00:16:18,202
I've been reading about emphysema.

206
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:19,834
You don't always die from it.

207
00:16:19,945 --> 00:16:21,970
Once will be enough.

208
00:16:22,081 --> 00:16:24,345
Italy has the worst air in Europe...

209
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:27,851
so many cars, motorbikes,
French restaurants.

210
00:16:27,953 --> 00:16:29,614
You should move to Scottsdale.

211
00:16:29,722 --> 00:16:32,350
- Where?
- It's the capital of Arizona.

212
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:34,426
Arizona? In America?

213
00:16:34,526 --> 00:16:37,518
It's a big open space with no cars.

214
00:16:37,629 --> 00:16:39,961
The air is clear, the days warm,

215
00:16:40,065 --> 00:16:43,364
the nights cool,
the sky filled with stars.

216
00:16:46,472 --> 00:16:47,461
So healthy.

217
00:16:49,108 --> 00:16:50,575
If only we had the money...

218
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:55,107
Eh, I go and get the vase.

219
00:16:57,483 --> 00:16:59,576
Think of it...
swimming pools,

220
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,050
cable television,

221
00:17:01,153 --> 00:17:03,314
28 flavors of ice cream.

222
00:17:03,422 --> 00:17:05,083
In two months,
you'll be bowling!

223
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:08,819
I don't want to be buried
under cactus.

224
00:17:08,927 --> 00:17:11,395
I want to die in Italy.

225
00:17:19,438 --> 00:17:22,839
Pavone, what are you doing?!
Are you crazy or what?

226
00:17:22,941 --> 00:17:25,341
Are you trying to kill yourself
and everybody else?

227
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:27,275
That's oxygen in your nose!

228
00:17:27,379 --> 00:17:29,370
I'm going to die anyway.

229
00:17:29,481 --> 00:17:32,507
Yes, but you'll blow up
your nose, then your head,

230
00:17:32,618 --> 00:17:34,017
then the whole hospital.

231
00:17:34,119 --> 00:17:38,021
And in one minute you'll fill up
the old cemetery and the new one!

232
00:17:43,128 --> 00:17:44,595
Gianna, you talk to him.

233
00:17:50,469 --> 00:17:52,369
I just heard. I'm sorry.

234
00:17:52,471 --> 00:17:55,497
- I gave him blood, you know.
- We are in your debt.

235
00:17:55,607 --> 00:17:57,472
It's the least I could do.

236
00:17:57,576 --> 00:17:59,373
He was a wonderful man.

237
00:17:59,478 --> 00:18:02,641
When he worked for us as a waiter,
the tourists loved him.

238
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:04,147
The way he flirted with them,

239
00:18:04,249 --> 00:18:05,978
they all felt
he wanted to marry them.

240
00:18:08,821 --> 00:18:11,619
But of course he didn't.
You'd already captured his heart.

241
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:14,859
So when will they...

242
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:18,922
Soon.

243
00:18:19,031 --> 00:18:20,498
May I say good-bye?

244
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:26,833
Good-bye, my old friend.

245
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:29,703
Godspeed till we meet again.

246
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:34,245
What?

247
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:36,038
- What?
- What?

248
00:18:36,148 --> 00:18:38,048
Nothing.
I just thought I heard...

249
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:39,174
What?

250
00:18:39,284 --> 00:18:42,742
I don't know.
It sounded like "bye-bye. "

251
00:18:42,855 --> 00:18:45,187
Paolo! Paolo!

252
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:47,281
Go call the doctor, quick!

253
00:18:47,392 --> 00:18:49,189
It was probably nothing.

254
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:51,785
Maybe I just got excited
when he squeezed my hand.

255
00:18:51,897 --> 00:18:53,023
He squeezed your hand?

256
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,828
I don't want to
raise false hopes if it's time.

257
00:18:56,902 --> 00:18:58,927
One second ago,
he squeezed his hand.

258
00:18:59,037 --> 00:19:01,335
He spoke!
He's coming back to life!

259
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,930
It's a miracle!
He's said "bye-bye"!

260
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:06,135
- Maybe it was just a belch.
- It's a miracle!

261
00:19:31,103 --> 00:19:33,003
Hello, my baby.

262
00:19:33,105 --> 00:19:36,336
God gave you tightrope walkers
to play with, huh?

263
00:19:36,441 --> 00:19:38,602
Don't stand under them.

264
00:19:39,711 --> 00:19:41,338
All right, let me see...

265
00:19:41,446 --> 00:19:46,349
The news... Lilia Palumbo
was confirmed on Sunday.

266
00:19:46,451 --> 00:19:48,783
Oh, darling,
she looked so beautiful.

267
00:19:48,887 --> 00:19:50,855
White dress.

268
00:19:50,956 --> 00:19:53,857
Maybe a little bit
too much lace on it.

269
00:19:53,959 --> 00:19:55,722
You know her mother.

270
00:19:58,964 --> 00:20:01,228
Oh, my darling...

271
00:20:03,802 --> 00:20:05,269
Little girl.

272
00:20:07,973 --> 00:20:11,238
Your papa and I miss you so much.

273
00:20:13,979 --> 00:20:17,915
Only the thought of being with you
makes me less afraid.

274
00:20:19,985 --> 00:20:23,716
And I am going to be
right here next to you.

275
00:20:23,822 --> 00:20:26,916
Your father is seeing to that.

276
00:20:28,493 --> 00:20:30,620
Because he's a magnificent man.

277
00:20:33,999 --> 00:20:35,261
A little crazy...

278
00:20:37,669 --> 00:20:39,296
but magnificent.

279
00:22:27,079 --> 00:22:29,047
<i>Puccini. La Traviata.</i>

280
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:34,152
Caruso?

281
00:22:36,221 --> 00:22:37,654
Pavarotti.

282
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:42,288
What are you doing here?

283
00:22:42,394 --> 00:22:44,362
The door was open.

284
00:22:44,463 --> 00:22:48,160
Such a beautiful house.
I don't think I have ever been inside.

285
00:22:50,569 --> 00:22:51,968
No accident.

286
00:22:55,207 --> 00:22:56,367
State your business.

287
00:22:59,344 --> 00:23:01,710
You have disliked me
for many years, Virgilio.

288
00:23:01,813 --> 00:23:03,041
No secret.

289
00:23:03,148 --> 00:23:06,311
I know the reason, of course.

290
00:23:06,418 --> 00:23:08,818
You blame me for your fall.

291
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,319
What fall?

292
00:23:10,422 --> 00:23:11,855
The cycle race.

293
00:23:11,957 --> 00:23:14,357
The last bend
on the downhill run.

294
00:23:15,794 --> 00:23:18,991
- It cost me the race.
- You could be right, huh.

295
00:23:19,097 --> 00:23:22,225
May I sit?
This is not easy for me.

296
00:23:26,304 --> 00:23:29,137
Lately I've been having dreams,

297
00:23:29,241 --> 00:23:31,709
the same dream each time.

298
00:23:31,810 --> 00:23:33,835
I see the race
as if it was yesterday.

299
00:23:33,945 --> 00:23:36,505
I hear the crowd,
I see the bikes flashing by.

300
00:23:36,615 --> 00:23:40,176
But, uh, when the winner
breaks the tape,

301
00:23:40,285 --> 00:23:42,810
it is you, Virgilio.

302
00:23:44,689 --> 00:23:46,850
I suppose my conscience
is telling me that, uh,

303
00:23:46,958 --> 00:23:48,357
you could have won.

304
00:23:49,461 --> 00:23:51,361
You were the best.

305
00:23:52,864 --> 00:23:54,923
Why are you telling me
this now?

306
00:23:57,002 --> 00:23:58,867
Maybe because of
my wife's illness.

307
00:23:58,970 --> 00:24:02,098
A man becomes aware
of mortality,

308
00:24:02,207 --> 00:24:04,072
a man wants to set
the record straight.

309
00:24:04,176 --> 00:24:07,145
He doesn't want to live
with a lie in his heart.

310
00:24:07,245 --> 00:24:08,212
Ahh.

311
00:24:11,917 --> 00:24:13,407
This is for you, Virgilio.

312
00:24:15,253 --> 00:24:17,721
You should have had it
all those years ago.

313
00:24:19,925 --> 00:24:23,326
It's certainly Roseanna's illness
that brought you here,

314
00:24:23,428 --> 00:24:25,828
but if you think I'm selling
my land to the church,

315
00:24:25,931 --> 00:24:28,024
you are a fool,
as well as a bullshitter.

316
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:31,967
How can you turn down
50 million lire for half an acre of wheat?

317
00:24:32,070 --> 00:24:33,367
You could travel with that money.

318
00:24:33,472 --> 00:24:36,270
You could go to La Scala, Milano,
and see Pavarotti up close,

319
00:24:36,374 --> 00:24:39,741
with all those big ladies
with fat chests.

320
00:24:40,846 --> 00:24:43,212
I would rather ride
across my land.

321
00:24:43,315 --> 00:24:45,044
If you don't own any,

322
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:47,618
you don't know what
it means to a man.

323
00:24:47,719 --> 00:24:52,213
Just tell me this...
how much will it take?

324
00:24:56,328 --> 00:24:58,888
More than you'll ever have.

325
00:24:59,965 --> 00:25:02,991
Now... get out
before I piss in your cup.

326
00:25:10,976 --> 00:25:13,001
You know something,
Capestro?

327
00:25:14,079 --> 00:25:17,810
If I had padlocked both of my wheels
and ridden without a saddle,

328
00:25:17,916 --> 00:25:20,749
I would have still whipped your ass.

329
00:25:52,384 --> 00:25:54,011
There you go, laccoponi.

330
00:25:54,119 --> 00:25:56,383
The sum total of your life.

331
00:25:58,623 --> 00:26:00,352
90,000 lire?

332
00:26:00,458 --> 00:26:03,120
I never walked around
with as little as this in my pocket.

333
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:04,217
Where's the rest of it?

334
00:26:04,329 --> 00:26:05,660
That's all there was.

335
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:08,456
You're all thieves.

336
00:26:08,567 --> 00:26:12,401
But we don't kidnap people
and cut off their ears.

337
00:26:12,504 --> 00:26:14,472
One ear.

338
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:15,904
And the guy got it back.

339
00:26:17,075 --> 00:26:19,475
So where are you going,
old man?

340
00:26:21,446 --> 00:26:22,674
South, maybe.

341
00:26:22,781 --> 00:26:25,011
Get some sun
on these old bones.

342
00:26:25,116 --> 00:26:28,381
Get a chair on the beach,
a liter of wine, watch the sunset.

343
00:26:28,486 --> 00:26:30,181
And dig up the ransom money?

344
00:26:30,288 --> 00:26:33,018
What are you talking about?

345
00:26:33,124 --> 00:26:34,614
They never found it.

346
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:38,354
You bet your ass the cops did,
and never filed a report.

347
00:26:38,463 --> 00:26:41,523
Those sons of bitches
probably carved it up

348
00:26:41,633 --> 00:26:43,396
and bought villas in Portofino,

349
00:26:43,501 --> 00:26:45,401
and what have I got?

350
00:26:45,503 --> 00:26:47,334
A watch that don't go...

351
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:49,339
a corkscrew...

352
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:53,571
and a ticket for shoe repairs
I took in 20 years ago.

353
00:26:53,678 --> 00:26:56,545
You're gonna need them.

354
00:27:06,925 --> 00:27:09,621
You shouldn't have gone there.
That man despises us.

355
00:27:09,728 --> 00:27:12,788
How could you expose
yourself to his contempt?

356
00:27:12,897 --> 00:27:16,298
You know why I went.
I'll try anything.

357
00:27:16,401 --> 00:27:19,461
There are limits!
Where is your pride?

358
00:27:19,571 --> 00:27:21,801
What's pride got to do with it?

359
00:27:21,906 --> 00:27:23,874
I thought he might
listen to reason.

360
00:27:23,975 --> 00:27:28,605
He is dead to reason!
He's not half the man you are!

361
00:27:28,713 --> 00:27:30,442
Then why are we fighting?

362
00:27:30,548 --> 00:27:31,981
We're not fighting!

363
00:27:36,821 --> 00:27:38,914
I just get angry sometimes.

364
00:27:41,092 --> 00:27:43,060
I get angry at the doctors.

365
00:27:43,161 --> 00:27:45,652
I get angry at my body.

366
00:27:46,865 --> 00:27:48,924
I get angry at God.

367
00:27:51,536 --> 00:27:54,437
Oh, darling,
what's happening to us?

368
00:27:57,809 --> 00:28:01,506
First we lose our daughter,
and now we're losing each other.

369
00:28:01,613 --> 00:28:03,410
We'll never lose each other.

370
00:28:07,919 --> 00:28:09,910
Listen to me, Marcello.

371
00:28:11,456 --> 00:28:14,755
You are a man
who should be married.

372
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:16,793
I am married.

373
00:28:16,895 --> 00:28:19,796
I don't want you to be alone.

374
00:28:19,898 --> 00:28:22,867
I don't want you to end up
a lonely old man

375
00:28:22,967 --> 00:28:24,798
with photographs and memories.

376
00:28:24,903 --> 00:28:26,632
I want you to live.

377
00:28:26,738 --> 00:28:29,036
I don't want to think about it.

378
00:28:29,140 --> 00:28:31,631
I want you to think
about it, Marcello.

379
00:28:31,743 --> 00:28:33,472
I'm worried about you.

380
00:28:33,578 --> 00:28:35,808
I'm worried about Cecilia.

381
00:28:35,914 --> 00:28:37,313
Don't worry about her.

382
00:28:37,415 --> 00:28:39,508
She'll go back to Roma
and marry a hairdresser.

383
00:28:39,617 --> 00:28:42,643
She's a beautiful woman.
She's sensitive.

384
00:28:42,754 --> 00:28:44,346
She doesn't dust off shelves.

385
00:28:44,456 --> 00:28:47,789
She would make you
a wonderful wife.

386
00:28:49,327 --> 00:28:51,318
Did they change
your medication today,

387
00:28:51,429 --> 00:28:54,796
or did you smoke that stuff
the Dutch tourists left behind?

388
00:28:54,899 --> 00:28:56,298
I'm serious, Marcello.

389
00:28:56,401 --> 00:28:58,062
I don't even like her.

390
00:28:58,169 --> 00:29:00,399
Well, of course I like her.
She's your sister.

391
00:29:00,505 --> 00:29:02,405
But not in that way.

392
00:29:02,507 --> 00:29:05,135
You already said that
you thought that she was sexy.

393
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:07,302
I didn't. You tricked me.

394
00:29:07,412 --> 00:29:10,904
And if you want me to marry again,
at least give me a choice.

395
00:29:11,015 --> 00:29:12,710
Why? You have
someone in mind?

396
00:29:12,817 --> 00:29:14,785
- Yes.
- Oh!

397
00:29:14,886 --> 00:29:17,184
Is it that girl
who cleans your teeth?

398
00:29:25,764 --> 00:29:28,096
He had breakfast,
bought some things in a pharmacy,

399
00:29:28,199 --> 00:29:30,064
and now he's in a shoe store.

400
00:29:35,874 --> 00:29:36,932
He's arguing.

401
00:29:38,943 --> 00:29:40,376
He's making a move.

402
00:29:49,020 --> 00:29:51,648
Police. The guy
who was just here...

403
00:29:51,756 --> 00:29:52,950
did he pick something up?

404
00:29:53,057 --> 00:29:57,357
He brought in a ticket
for shoe repairs from 20 years ago.

405
00:29:57,462 --> 00:29:59,020
What did you tell him?

406
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:01,428
I could see you arguing
through the window.

407
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:05,025
I told him
they'd be ready Tuesday.

408
00:30:18,449 --> 00:30:20,440
How much are the melons
today, Gigi?

409
00:30:20,552 --> 00:30:22,747
500 to you.
1,200 to the tourists.

410
00:30:22,854 --> 00:30:24,082
I'll have four.

411
00:30:24,189 --> 00:30:27,955
<i>Mi scusi. They are selling
for 400 in Gevarro.</i>

412
00:30:28,059 --> 00:30:30,459
How about it, Gigi?
400 each.

413
00:30:30,562 --> 00:30:33,963
And who will you thank,
me or your lawyer?

414
00:30:34,065 --> 00:30:35,965
I didn't know I'd hired one.

415
00:30:36,067 --> 00:30:37,625
It's a deal then.

416
00:30:37,735 --> 00:30:39,327
Today you look like a lawyer.

417
00:30:39,437 --> 00:30:41,564
This is my first week.

418
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:44,073
What, looking after
your uncle's tax problems?

419
00:30:45,476 --> 00:30:46,738
Listen, Cecilia,

420
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:48,745
I hope you won't let
your feelings for my uncle

421
00:30:48,847 --> 00:30:50,405
affect your feelings for me.

422
00:30:50,515 --> 00:30:51,504
Feelings?

423
00:30:51,616 --> 00:30:53,914
I was hoping
we could have dinner tonight.

424
00:30:54,018 --> 00:30:55,508
I have to work.

425
00:30:56,754 --> 00:30:58,585
You're not making this
very easy for me.

426
00:30:59,691 --> 00:31:01,420
Maybe another time?

427
00:31:04,295 --> 00:31:05,853
Antonio.

428
00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:08,159
What kind of fish do you like?

429
00:31:20,278 --> 00:31:22,337
Signor Rossi, telephone.

430
00:31:26,117 --> 00:31:27,675
Rossi. Hello?

431
00:31:28,953 --> 00:31:30,853
Hello, Bruno.

432
00:31:30,955 --> 00:31:32,855
It's Fredo laccoponi.

433
00:31:32,957 --> 00:31:34,754
Fredo!

434
00:31:36,127 --> 00:31:37,617
Where are you?

435
00:31:40,298 --> 00:31:42,266
You... you'll be here when?

436
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:57,305
I'm gonna take a leak,

437
00:31:57,415 --> 00:31:59,815
and then I'm getting
the 11:30 train to Roma.

438
00:31:59,918 --> 00:32:01,977
Maybe you want
to call your wives,

439
00:32:02,086 --> 00:32:04,350
tell them you won't
be home for dinner.

440
00:32:11,296 --> 00:32:13,196
What will Marcello say
when you tell him

441
00:32:13,298 --> 00:32:15,198
you invited
a Capestro to dinner?

442
00:32:15,300 --> 00:32:18,235
He's not his son.
Only his nephew.

443
00:32:18,336 --> 00:32:20,736
Think I put too much garlic
in this sauce?

444
00:32:20,838 --> 00:32:22,738
You can't put
too much garlic in anything.

445
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:25,240
- You like him?
- Not especially.

446
00:32:25,343 --> 00:32:26,901
Why did you invite him?

447
00:32:27,011 --> 00:32:28,911
Because he likes me,
and maybe I can convince him

448
00:32:29,013 --> 00:32:30,913
to talk some sense
into his uncle.

449
00:32:31,015 --> 00:32:32,846
Shame on you.

450
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:34,919
When did you become
such a person?

451
00:32:35,019 --> 00:32:38,011
When the family Tanzini
left the high wire.

452
00:32:39,123 --> 00:32:40,090
Hmm.

453
00:32:40,191 --> 00:32:42,557
<i>Maybe you and Marcello
are made for each other.</i>

454
00:32:42,660 --> 00:32:44,457
Not again, Rosa, please.

455
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:47,929
Why? Why do you always
object to him that way?

456
00:32:48,032 --> 00:32:49,932
He's a beautiful man.

457
00:32:50,034 --> 00:32:53,435
The first time I came in here
when I was a girl,

458
00:32:53,538 --> 00:32:54,766
he served me coffee,

459
00:32:54,872 --> 00:32:57,204
I couldn't get my hand
to take it from him.

460
00:32:58,676 --> 00:33:00,576
I froze.

461
00:33:00,678 --> 00:33:02,168
You ever had that?

462
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:05,943
Just for a moment,
the world stops.

463
00:33:06,050 --> 00:33:07,483
For you, Roseanna.

464
00:33:07,585 --> 00:33:10,486
<i>Marcello doesn't even make
my world slow down.</i>

465
00:33:10,588 --> 00:33:12,317
- What, you hate him?
- No.

466
00:33:12,423 --> 00:33:14,152
All right. That's a start.

467
00:33:14,258 --> 00:33:16,726
You haven't said
anything to him about this?

468
00:33:16,828 --> 00:33:18,989
No, no, of course not.

469
00:33:23,534 --> 00:33:25,229
Roseanna asked me,
and I told her the church

470
00:33:25,336 --> 00:33:27,497
would have no problem
if you married her sister.

471
00:33:27,605 --> 00:33:29,971
Is there anyone
she hasn't talked to about this?

472
00:33:30,074 --> 00:33:31,974
I heard rumors.

473
00:33:32,076 --> 00:33:33,509
You know something?

474
00:33:33,611 --> 00:33:35,169
If I give the slightest sign

475
00:33:35,279 --> 00:33:37,509
I thought it was a good idea,
she'd be furious.

476
00:33:37,615 --> 00:33:38,843
I don't understand.

477
00:33:38,950 --> 00:33:40,247
It's a test.

478
00:33:40,351 --> 00:33:42,649
Celibacy is so uncomplicated.

479
00:33:43,755 --> 00:33:45,655
Father, Marcello,
come quickly.

480
00:33:45,757 --> 00:33:46,985
What is it?

481
00:33:47,091 --> 00:33:48,649
It's Pasquale!
He climbed the tower!

482
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:50,625
And he's threatening to jump!

483
00:33:55,633 --> 00:33:57,601
I'm gonna jump!

484
00:33:57,702 --> 00:33:59,932
- Pasquale, what are you doing?
- I'll talk to him.

485
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,507
I'm gonna jump!

486
00:34:03,608 --> 00:34:05,166
He's worried about his exams.

487
00:34:05,276 --> 00:34:07,676
Pasquale, what's this nonsense
about your exams?

488
00:34:07,779 --> 00:34:11,044
I know they're a pain in the ass,
but let me tell you something...

489
00:34:11,149 --> 00:34:13,049
I've never passed
an exam in my life,

490
00:34:13,151 --> 00:34:15,119
and look what I am today.

491
00:34:16,587 --> 00:34:18,714
Okay, that wasn't
a very good example.

492
00:34:19,090 --> 00:34:22,059
But you can be
anything you wish! Believe me!

493
00:34:22,160 --> 00:34:24,151
But everybody hates me!

494
00:34:24,262 --> 00:34:25,889
No, they don't! They don't!

495
00:34:25,997 --> 00:34:28,522
Look at all these people!
We're all your friends!

496
00:34:28,633 --> 00:34:30,100
And think of your father!

497
00:34:30,201 --> 00:34:33,227
Only last night, he told me
how proud he is of you!

498
00:34:33,337 --> 00:34:35,202
But my father's in Torino.

499
00:34:36,441 --> 00:34:38,534
We spoke on the phone!
Listen!

500
00:34:38,643 --> 00:34:40,474
Pasquale,
you come down! Now!

501
00:34:48,152 --> 00:34:49,813
Okay.

502
00:34:53,157 --> 00:34:54,385
What's going on?

503
00:35:05,403 --> 00:35:06,802
Marcello, Marcello!

504
00:35:16,914 --> 00:35:19,314
Roseanna, where are those pills
the doctor gave me?

505
00:35:19,417 --> 00:35:21,044
What pills?

506
00:35:21,152 --> 00:35:23,347
The ones to calm me down.

507
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:25,547
Which are mine,
and which are yours?

508
00:35:25,656 --> 00:35:27,419
I can't see
without my glasses.

509
00:35:29,127 --> 00:35:30,355
They're both mine.

510
00:35:30,495 --> 00:35:31,860
I need them.

511
00:35:31,963 --> 00:35:35,364
Do you know what those kids
did to my blood pressure?

512
00:35:35,466 --> 00:35:37,866
I'm calling their fathers
and the school principal.

513
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:41,996
And then I come home and I find
a Capestro is coming to dinner.

514
00:35:42,106 --> 00:35:44,097
Try the closet on the landing, hmm.

515
00:35:44,208 --> 00:35:46,142
Roseanna, Roseanna,
Roseanna...

516
00:35:46,244 --> 00:35:48,644
Why are you getting
your own towels?

517
00:35:48,746 --> 00:35:52,273
You're a guest in my house.
Guests don't get their own towels.

518
00:35:53,184 --> 00:35:54,151
Hmm.

519
00:35:55,686 --> 00:35:56,778
Hmm.

520
00:35:56,888 --> 00:35:58,355
<i>Mamma mia.</i>

521
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:00,916
You find them?

522
00:36:06,430 --> 00:36:08,625
Are you angry because
her guest is a Capestro

523
00:36:08,733 --> 00:36:10,200
or because he's another man?

524
00:36:10,301 --> 00:36:12,269
Am I what? Are you crazy?

525
00:36:12,370 --> 00:36:16,067
Then try to be nice.
She's doing this for me, Marcello.

526
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:19,507
Try to be charming.
And give him your good wine.

527
00:36:19,610 --> 00:36:21,635
I'd sooner give him rat poison.

528
00:36:21,746 --> 00:36:23,543
And then we lose another grave.

529
00:36:43,434 --> 00:36:45,766
<i>- Yes?
- Bruno. It's me.</i>

530
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:47,337
Oh! Francesca.

531
00:36:47,438 --> 00:36:48,996
<i>What's wrong?
You sound strange.</i>

532
00:36:49,106 --> 00:36:51,165
No, no, no. I'm all right.

533
00:36:51,275 --> 00:36:54,005
It's just...
this isn't a good time.

534
00:36:54,111 --> 00:36:55,510
<i>Can we go to Sardinia?</i>

535
00:36:55,613 --> 00:36:58,343
Of course. I'm excited.

536
00:36:58,449 --> 00:37:00,349
I can't wait to see you.

537
00:37:00,451 --> 00:37:01,782
Let me call you later.

538
00:37:01,886 --> 00:37:02,853
<i>H'm not in.</i>

539
00:37:02,954 --> 00:37:04,785
<i>- You'll be out?
- With my brother.</i>

540
00:37:04,889 --> 00:37:06,857
<i>- Tomorrow, then.
- Ciao.</i>

541
00:37:30,314 --> 00:37:32,214
You went away.
You saw the world.

542
00:37:32,316 --> 00:37:34,716
Why did you come back here?

543
00:37:34,819 --> 00:37:36,377
It's home.
I always missed it.

544
00:37:36,487 --> 00:37:39,388
I couldn't wait to get away. I only
came back because of my sister.

545
00:37:39,490 --> 00:37:42,516
Marcello's lucky to have
two such beautiful women in his life.

546
00:37:42,627 --> 00:37:45,994
Yes, he often goes to church
to make a special offering of thanks.

547
00:37:47,031 --> 00:37:49,295
So what do you think?
They're happy?

548
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,561
- Good. Good.
- Yeah?

549
00:37:56,173 --> 00:37:59,199
- Oh, Marcello!
- We were having fun.

550
00:38:05,816 --> 00:38:08,444
- This is not right.
- What is not right?

551
00:38:08,552 --> 00:38:12,215
Cecilia prostituting herself
for your grave.

552
00:38:12,323 --> 00:38:15,486
Maybe she'll succeed
where the priest and Marcello failed.

553
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:18,289
You know, a few years ago,

554
00:38:18,396 --> 00:38:20,193
I wouldn't have
believed this possible.

555
00:38:20,298 --> 00:38:23,290
You seemed so aloof and unobtainable,
surrounded by admirers.

556
00:38:23,401 --> 00:38:25,801
- Where's this?
- At school.

557
00:38:25,903 --> 00:38:27,370
I was very shy.

558
00:38:27,471 --> 00:38:29,371
L... I wore glasses.
Of course, you were...

559
00:38:29,473 --> 00:38:32,772
The Risotto alla Cecilia.
Her own recipe.

560
00:38:37,782 --> 00:38:39,579
I'm very flattered.

561
00:38:51,295 --> 00:38:54,196
I don't have a car,
and I can't afford a hotel room.

562
00:38:54,298 --> 00:38:57,096
I'm sure I have something
for whatever you've got.

563
00:39:04,842 --> 00:39:06,400
It's been a long time.

564
00:39:06,510 --> 00:39:08,910
You might have to
remind me how it's done.

565
00:39:09,013 --> 00:39:11,447
It'll come back to you.

566
00:39:48,619 --> 00:39:50,382
- More wine, Antonio?
- Oh, I don't think so.

567
00:39:50,488 --> 00:39:53,889
- I have to work tomorrow.
- For justice or for your uncle?

568
00:39:53,991 --> 00:39:56,892
The trouble with working for my uncle
is he always expects a discount.

569
00:39:56,994 --> 00:39:58,894
It's funny how the rich
always get a discount

570
00:39:58,996 --> 00:40:00,861
and the poor
have to pay full price.

571
00:40:00,965 --> 00:40:02,933
Well, I'm sure he trusts you.

572
00:40:03,033 --> 00:40:05,331
He seems to trust so few people.

573
00:40:05,436 --> 00:40:06,960
Cecilia.

574
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:09,471
Is this evening about the land?

575
00:40:09,573 --> 00:40:11,165
What do you mean?

576
00:40:12,309 --> 00:40:14,209
The candlelight. The music.

577
00:40:14,311 --> 00:40:17,041
Is this for me or because
you think I'll influence my uncle?

578
00:40:17,148 --> 00:40:18,342
It's for you.

579
00:40:19,917 --> 00:40:22,283
Well, maybe I was hoping
it could be for both.

580
00:40:22,386 --> 00:40:24,786
This is our best grappa.
20 years old.

581
00:40:24,889 --> 00:40:26,789
We call it the piss of the goat.

582
00:40:26,891 --> 00:40:29,519
So. How is it going
with you two, huh?

583
00:40:31,495 --> 00:40:34,089
I think we understand
each other.

584
00:40:34,198 --> 00:40:36,428
Fantastic. So you'll talk
to your uncle tomorrow.

585
00:40:40,137 --> 00:40:41,434
Perhaps another time.

586
00:40:43,641 --> 00:40:45,199
Good night, Cecilia.

587
00:40:45,309 --> 00:40:46,276
Good night.

588
00:40:51,015 --> 00:40:53,040
What's happening here?
Did I say something?

589
00:40:53,150 --> 00:40:55,243
You're a fool, Marcello,
and he isn't.

590
00:40:55,352 --> 00:40:57,752
And you know something?
I shouldn't have done this.

591
00:41:07,131 --> 00:41:08,564
Antonio, I'm sorry.

592
00:41:10,968 --> 00:41:14,597
Half an acre! That's all they want
off the miserable son of a bitch!

593
00:41:30,154 --> 00:41:32,054
It's me. I can get a train

594
00:41:32,156 --> 00:41:34,124
and be with you
in a couple of hours.

595
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:37,149
Why not?

596
00:41:37,261 --> 00:41:39,058
I need time.

597
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:41,222
I made investments.

598
00:41:41,332 --> 00:41:43,892
I need 24 hours
to give you cash.

599
00:41:44,001 --> 00:41:45,161
Okay.

600
00:41:55,346 --> 00:41:57,746
- It's good sauce, huh?
- Yes.

601
00:41:57,848 --> 00:41:59,076
Cecilia made it.

602
00:42:00,184 --> 00:42:02,778
She didn't make it.
You made it.

603
00:42:02,887 --> 00:42:04,218
Will you stop this?

604
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:09,424
Marcello, come quick. It's Rossi.
He's drunk, and he's out of control.

605
00:42:10,895 --> 00:42:11,862
He's crazy!

606
00:42:11,962 --> 00:42:14,795
- Why does this happen to me?!
- What's going on?

607
00:42:14,899 --> 00:42:16,662
I just had to be happy!

608
00:42:16,767 --> 00:42:18,598
Stop breaking my dishes!

609
00:42:19,703 --> 00:42:23,104
Here! Buy more dishes,
buy glasses, buy plates!

610
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:24,469
What's wrong with him?

611
00:42:24,575 --> 00:42:26,372
It's something about a woman.

612
00:42:26,477 --> 00:42:27,876
Bruno, you are distraught.

613
00:42:27,978 --> 00:42:29,206
We're your friends.

614
00:42:29,313 --> 00:42:30,871
What is this all about?

615
00:42:30,981 --> 00:42:32,881
A man looks at his life

616
00:42:32,983 --> 00:42:35,178
and wonders where
all his dreams went.

617
00:42:35,286 --> 00:42:37,777
But you have a good life.
You have a good position.

618
00:42:37,888 --> 00:42:40,482
I'm a big fish in a very small pond.

619
00:42:40,591 --> 00:42:42,684
Nothing wrong with
living in a small pond.

620
00:42:43,727 --> 00:42:46,161
Ask him about the mistress.

621
00:42:47,231 --> 00:42:49,222
What? Is it true?

622
00:42:50,601 --> 00:42:52,398
You have a mistress?

623
00:42:52,503 --> 00:42:54,198
It's true.

624
00:42:54,305 --> 00:42:56,432
Oh, she's beautiful.

625
00:42:58,309 --> 00:43:00,869
Firm breasts...
soft thighs...

626
00:43:01,812 --> 00:43:03,973
Bruno, you're
a widower, remember?

627
00:43:04,081 --> 00:43:06,641
She sounds wonderful!
Bring her over! Bring...

628
00:43:07,685 --> 00:43:08,913
<i>Oh Dio...</i>

629
00:43:11,088 --> 00:43:12,749
She was my mistress
when Nina was alive.

630
00:43:12,856 --> 00:43:13,823
<i>Si. Si.</i>

631
00:43:13,924 --> 00:43:16,859
She was the girl in the beauty shop!
Francesca! I remember!

632
00:43:16,961 --> 00:43:18,189
I remember!

633
00:43:19,296 --> 00:43:20,820
My God.

634
00:43:20,931 --> 00:43:22,558
So why are you acting like this?

635
00:43:23,934 --> 00:43:26,425
Because she has ruined my life!

636
00:43:29,006 --> 00:43:29,973
Aah!

637
00:43:31,609 --> 00:43:32,576
Yaa!

638
00:43:33,110 --> 00:43:34,077
He's mad!

639
00:43:38,849 --> 00:43:40,316
Bruno! Bruno, wait!

640
00:43:43,020 --> 00:43:44,920
Wait! You're
too drunk to drive.

641
00:43:45,022 --> 00:43:46,512
You'll kill yourself.

642
00:43:47,625 --> 00:43:51,425
What's the difference?
I'm gonna die anyway!

643
00:43:51,528 --> 00:43:54,292
Not before Roseanna, you're not.

644
00:44:00,337 --> 00:44:01,964
Stop torturing yourself.

645
00:44:02,072 --> 00:44:04,700
See the priest,
do your penance,

646
00:44:04,808 --> 00:44:06,708
then you can
call her your girlfriend.

647
00:44:06,810 --> 00:44:07,834
Where is she?

648
00:44:07,945 --> 00:44:09,879
In the apartment
I bought for her in Rome.

649
00:44:09,980 --> 00:44:11,709
You bought her an apartment?

650
00:44:11,815 --> 00:44:12,782
Yes.

651
00:44:12,883 --> 00:44:16,148
And what, she still stays alone
and waits for you?

652
00:44:16,253 --> 00:44:18,551
No, her brother moved in.

653
00:44:18,656 --> 00:44:20,453
They're a very loving family.

654
00:44:21,492 --> 00:44:22,584
But we go on trips.

655
00:44:22,693 --> 00:44:25,628
This week we are
leaving for Sardinia.

656
00:44:25,729 --> 00:44:27,526
Where did you find
the money for this?

657
00:44:30,334 --> 00:44:33,201
Don't tell me. You've been
stealing from the bank.

658
00:44:33,303 --> 00:44:35,430
Worse! Worse.

659
00:44:35,539 --> 00:44:37,063
Worse?

660
00:44:38,175 --> 00:44:41,667
Twenty years ago, I look after
some money for some kidnappers.

661
00:44:41,779 --> 00:44:42,939
When they went to jail,

662
00:44:43,047 --> 00:44:45,311
I was supposed to invest it,
build interest.

663
00:44:45,416 --> 00:44:48,249
And for five years, I did that,
Marcello, I swear it. I swear it!

664
00:44:48,352 --> 00:44:50,616
I believe you,
I believe you! Calm down!

665
00:44:51,722 --> 00:44:53,349
Calm down!

666
00:44:53,457 --> 00:44:56,984
Then I met Francesca,
and my life changed.

667
00:44:57,094 --> 00:45:00,029
I told myself,
They'll die in jail.

668
00:45:00,130 --> 00:45:02,928
Eh, so I started
spending money on her.

669
00:45:03,033 --> 00:45:04,466
But one of them didn't die!

670
00:45:04,568 --> 00:45:07,002
He's out,
and he wants his money!

671
00:45:07,104 --> 00:45:08,128
How much are we
talking about?

672
00:45:08,238 --> 00:45:09,500
750 million lire.

673
00:45:09,606 --> 00:45:11,801
Shit, how much is left?

674
00:45:11,909 --> 00:45:14,275
Not enough to make him happy.

675
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:16,676
He's going to kill me,
Marcello!

676
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:18,372
You've got to get away
from here.

677
00:45:18,482 --> 00:45:21,178
You're right.
I'll see you later.

678
00:45:22,119 --> 00:45:23,609
No!

679
00:45:28,592 --> 00:45:30,116
Are you all right?

680
00:45:34,965 --> 00:45:36,455
Can you stand?

681
00:45:38,469 --> 00:45:39,436
I lost a shoe.

682
00:45:39,536 --> 00:45:41,436
Oh, you're lucky
it wasn't your life.

683
00:45:41,538 --> 00:45:43,005
Thank you, God.

684
00:45:57,855 --> 00:45:59,186
Bruno!

685
00:46:05,996 --> 00:46:07,759
Please don't be dead.

686
00:46:07,965 --> 00:46:08,954
Please don't be dead.

687
00:46:09,066 --> 00:46:10,499
Bruno...

688
00:46:11,769 --> 00:46:12,997
Oh, what was that?

689
00:46:13,103 --> 00:46:14,161
Oh, please.

690
00:46:14,271 --> 00:46:16,296
I don't feel so good.

691
00:46:16,406 --> 00:46:19,466
Oh, I'm going to find a phone
and call the hospital.

692
00:46:19,576 --> 00:46:21,476
If you need blood,
I'll give you mine.

693
00:46:21,578 --> 00:46:25,173
Marcello, I want to be buried
with Nina in the cemetery.

694
00:46:25,282 --> 00:46:28,012
Oh, don't ask me that.
It's booked.

695
00:46:29,520 --> 00:46:31,420
I have some money left,

696
00:46:31,522 --> 00:46:34,787
money you could offer
to Capestro for his land.

697
00:46:34,892 --> 00:46:36,359
Where?

698
00:46:36,460 --> 00:46:40,419
First, you must promise to bury me
with my beloved Nina.

699
00:46:40,531 --> 00:46:43,523
Oh, but there are
only three plots left.

700
00:46:44,635 --> 00:46:48,469
Promise me, or that money
will rot where it's hidden.

701
00:46:48,572 --> 00:46:50,039
Okay, I promise you.

702
00:46:52,843 --> 00:46:55,141
- I promise you.
- Take an oath.

703
00:46:56,613 --> 00:46:59,081
I take a solemn oath to bury you
in the cemetery with Nina.

704
00:46:59,183 --> 00:47:01,014
So where is it?

705
00:47:01,118 --> 00:47:02,915
It's under my wife.

706
00:47:03,453 --> 00:47:04,750
Under your wife?

707
00:47:04,855 --> 00:47:08,655
My dear Nina,
whose memory I shamed.

708
00:47:10,227 --> 00:47:11,751
It's in her grave.

709
00:47:14,264 --> 00:47:15,231
Bruno.

710
00:47:16,967 --> 00:47:17,934
Bruno.

711
00:47:22,239 --> 00:47:23,206
Bruno.

712
00:47:46,964 --> 00:47:48,363
We still have to work on it.

713
00:47:48,465 --> 00:47:50,763
But it will be
better on Sunday

714
00:47:50,868 --> 00:47:53,132
if you move your lips,
Pasquale.

715
00:47:54,438 --> 00:47:56,804
Father, something terrible
has happened.

716
00:47:56,907 --> 00:47:58,966
I know, I know.
I'm on my way.

717
00:48:00,744 --> 00:48:02,575
But how do you know?

718
00:48:02,679 --> 00:48:04,544
The hospital telephoned.

719
00:48:04,648 --> 00:48:07,173
At least his wife
had time to prepare herself.

720
00:48:07,284 --> 00:48:08,308
Poor Gianna.

721
00:48:09,419 --> 00:48:11,284
Are you
talking about Pavone?

722
00:48:11,388 --> 00:48:13,856
Yes, and poor Aprea
will be next.

723
00:48:13,957 --> 00:48:15,686
Then the cemetery will be full.

724
00:48:15,792 --> 00:48:17,851
No, there are three places left.

725
00:48:17,961 --> 00:48:20,191
Yes, but if
somebody else died.

726
00:48:20,297 --> 00:48:21,764
Who else?

727
00:48:22,799 --> 00:48:25,199
I don't know,
but, uh, these things happen.

728
00:48:27,771 --> 00:48:31,172
Father, can you say
the last rites

729
00:48:31,275 --> 00:48:32,765
after somebody is dead?

730
00:48:32,876 --> 00:48:34,400
Well, I always
believed that the soul

731
00:48:34,511 --> 00:48:36,308
does not leave the body
just like that.

732
00:48:36,413 --> 00:48:37,437
There is time.

733
00:48:37,581 --> 00:48:40,209
Good, but what do you say
when you give the last rites?

734
00:48:40,317 --> 00:48:41,545
Marcello, don't worry.

735
00:48:41,652 --> 00:48:44,553
When Roseanna's time comes,
I'll be there.

736
00:48:44,655 --> 00:48:46,623
Thank you, but what do you say

737
00:48:46,723 --> 00:48:49,692
if the time comes
and you're not there?

738
00:48:49,793 --> 00:48:52,728
I say, "God bless this soul.
Take her into your kingdom. "

739
00:48:52,829 --> 00:48:54,888
That kind of thing.

740
00:48:54,998 --> 00:48:56,226
Thank you.

741
00:49:48,986 --> 00:49:51,352
Forgive me, Nina.
It's only temporary.

742
00:50:07,337 --> 00:50:10,272
God bless this soul
and take him into your kingdom.

743
00:50:10,374 --> 00:50:12,239
He didn't get a chance
to atone for his sins,

744
00:50:12,342 --> 00:50:13,969
but he would have atoned.

745
00:50:14,077 --> 00:50:15,544
He wasn't a terrible person,

746
00:50:15,645 --> 00:50:18,443
but as far as I know,
he was a good husband.

747
00:50:18,548 --> 00:50:21,016
You've seen Francesca.
Who can blame him?

748
00:50:25,722 --> 00:50:27,690
I forgot to say
this soul is Bruno Rossi.

749
00:50:54,718 --> 00:50:56,185
Where have you been?

750
00:50:56,386 --> 00:50:57,614
Where have I been?

751
00:50:57,721 --> 00:50:59,450
You know where I've been.
I drove Rossi home.

752
00:50:59,556 --> 00:51:01,114
That was four hours ago.

753
00:51:01,224 --> 00:51:03,351
He needed to talk man to man.

754
00:51:03,460 --> 00:51:04,825
About Francesca?

755
00:51:07,030 --> 00:51:09,123
You shouldn't be up.
You need your sleep.

756
00:51:14,738 --> 00:51:17,002
He has done something
he shouldn't.

757
00:51:17,107 --> 00:51:19,632
- How do you know?
- I can tell.

758
00:51:19,743 --> 00:51:21,335
I hope he's not cheating on you.

759
00:51:21,445 --> 00:51:24,573
Cheating on me?
You're his wife. I'm only his guest.

760
00:51:26,216 --> 00:51:27,547
Did he ever cheat on you?

761
00:51:28,952 --> 00:51:31,580
I don't think so.
You know Marcello.

762
00:51:31,688 --> 00:51:34,816
I know men.
Can you swear he never has?

763
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:40,491
Not with his whole body.
Just with his eyes.

764
00:51:40,597 --> 00:51:44,863
With his lips, once or twice,
but never with the private.

765
00:51:44,968 --> 00:51:46,230
