1016
01:10:43,072 --> 01:10:47,133
Wait! I want to see you
with it on. Please.

1017
01:10:49,378 --> 01:10:52,142
Oh, you're right.
It's made for you.

1018
01:10:52,248 --> 01:10:54,546
You look superb,
like a movie star.

1019
01:10:56,719 --> 01:10:59,017
May I say one thing...
if Rossi's cheating on you,

1020
01:10:59,121 --> 01:11:01,089
the man is a fool.

1021
01:11:02,491 --> 01:11:05,949
If you're ever in Roma,
look me up.

1022
01:11:07,263 --> 01:11:08,230
<i>Ciao.</i>

1023
01:11:13,636 --> 01:11:15,695
What a bitch!

1024
01:11:26,915 --> 01:11:28,314
How did you find that?

1025
01:11:31,020 --> 01:11:33,818
I'm asking the questions here.
Where's it come from?

1026
01:11:33,922 --> 01:11:36,550
It was ransom money
from a long time ago.

1027
01:11:36,659 --> 01:11:38,490
Rossi gave it to me
just before he died.

1028
01:11:38,594 --> 01:11:40,027
- He died?
- Yes.

1029
01:11:40,129 --> 01:11:42,927
- How?
- He was hit by his car.

1030
01:11:43,032 --> 01:11:45,296
I didn't say anything.
He'd take up a grave.

1031
01:11:45,401 --> 01:11:47,801
Half the province
is looking for him.

1032
01:11:47,903 --> 01:11:49,803
- Where is he?
- I put him in his deep freeze.

1033
01:11:49,905 --> 01:11:50,963
What?

1034
01:11:51,073 --> 01:11:53,701
To keep him fresh,
but don't worry,

1035
01:11:53,809 --> 01:11:56,243
I promised to bury him
next to his beloved Nina.

1036
01:11:56,345 --> 01:11:59,314
Maybe not next to her.
Maybe on the top.

1037
01:12:00,416 --> 01:12:02,680
You're going to bury a man
on top of his wife?

1038
01:12:02,785 --> 01:12:05,049
Well, it's not
an entirely unusual position.

1039
01:12:05,154 --> 01:12:07,918
Marcello,
what are you thinking of?

1040
01:12:08,023 --> 01:12:10,457
If he's not found,
he'll be a missing person.

1041
01:12:10,559 --> 01:12:12,789
There'd be no inheritance
for his children.

1042
01:12:12,895 --> 01:12:15,090
And he's got to have
a proper Christian burial.

1043
01:12:15,197 --> 01:12:17,495
Roseanna's right.
You can't deny a Catholic that.

1044
01:12:17,599 --> 01:12:19,533
- You heard all this?
- I couldn't help it.

1045
01:12:19,635 --> 01:12:20,727
God damn it!

1046
01:12:20,836 --> 01:12:23,771
I hate having people in this house
who are not married to me!

1047
01:12:23,872 --> 01:12:27,399
Quiet, quiet, quiet!
We're all in this together.

1048
01:12:27,509 --> 01:12:30,239
Yes, but what
are we going to do?

1049
01:12:30,346 --> 01:12:32,405
He's been in the freezer
for two days.

1050
01:12:35,517 --> 01:12:38,645
First thing we'll do
is pay a visit to the doctor.

1051
01:12:39,988 --> 01:12:41,580
Roseanna,

1052
01:12:41,690 --> 01:12:45,091
the timing on a death certificate,
it is crucial.

1053
01:12:45,194 --> 01:12:46,684
It has to be precise.

1054
01:12:46,795 --> 01:12:49,730
What difference does it make
if it's a few days off?

1055
01:12:49,832 --> 01:12:51,959
He's dead.
He can't come back to life.

1056
01:12:52,067 --> 01:12:53,728
I could lose my license,
my patients.

1057
01:12:53,836 --> 01:12:55,770
Nobody pays you
anyway, Sergio.

1058
01:12:58,207 --> 01:12:59,731
Why would Marcello do this?

1059
01:12:59,842 --> 01:13:01,639
You know why.

1060
01:13:04,813 --> 01:13:06,041
I'm sorry, Roseanna.

1061
01:13:06,148 --> 01:13:08,048
It's too important a document.

1062
01:13:08,150 --> 01:13:10,209
It's a piece of paper.

1063
01:13:10,319 --> 01:13:12,048
Do you think
a death certificate

1064
01:13:12,154 --> 01:13:15,453
should cause unnecessary
suffering to the living?

1065
01:13:16,492 --> 01:13:18,323
You look a little tired.

1066
01:13:19,361 --> 01:13:21,420
<i>You look exhausted.</i>

1067
01:13:21,530 --> 01:13:24,556
Sergio, take a vacation, eh?

1068
01:13:24,666 --> 01:13:26,566
You and Isabella.

1069
01:13:26,668 --> 01:13:28,158
Go to Capri.

1070
01:13:29,271 --> 01:13:30,329
In our dreams.

1071
01:13:30,439 --> 01:13:32,999
What if we settle our account?

1072
01:13:33,108 --> 01:13:34,837
Did you bring the chicken?

1073
01:13:47,189 --> 01:13:49,157
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

1074
01:13:52,694 --> 01:13:55,595
I want to thank you, Cecilia.

1075
01:13:55,697 --> 01:13:59,098
I can't think of another girl
who would have done this.

1076
01:13:59,201 --> 01:14:02,602
I think it helps to have company
when you're defrosting a corpse.

1077
01:14:07,976 --> 01:14:09,603
I have a lot to thank you for.

1078
01:14:09,711 --> 01:14:11,508
And I'm sorry for
what I said last night

1079
01:14:11,613 --> 01:14:13,774
about not wanting you
in my house.

1080
01:14:13,882 --> 01:14:16,942
I understand. It's difficult
when people live that close.

1081
01:14:17,052 --> 01:14:19,782
Do you hear a lot
of what we talk about?

1082
01:14:19,888 --> 01:14:23,449
I know what Roseanna
has in mind for you and me.

1083
01:14:23,559 --> 01:14:25,550
Oh, that.
Look, I have to tell you...

1084
01:14:25,661 --> 01:14:28,289
Listen, you don't have to
apologize for not wanting me.

1085
01:14:28,397 --> 01:14:30,661
Of course I want you!

1086
01:14:30,766 --> 01:14:32,165
Any man would.

1087
01:14:32,267 --> 01:14:33,859
What am I saying?

1088
01:14:33,969 --> 01:14:36,904
Listen, with people
it's a question of chemistry,

1089
01:14:37,005 --> 01:14:38,472
and it's not there.

1090
01:14:38,574 --> 01:14:40,474
Are you saying
I have no chemistry?

1091
01:14:40,576 --> 01:14:43,670
No, Marcello. You could
ignite a thousand hearts.

1092
01:14:43,779 --> 01:14:47,215
But admit it, there's
nothing between you and me.

1093
01:14:47,316 --> 01:14:49,910
I suppose so.

1094
01:14:50,018 --> 01:14:51,417
It's a relief, huh?

1095
01:14:51,520 --> 01:14:53,044
Definitely.

1096
01:14:55,491 --> 01:14:56,924
Now we can be friends, huh?

1097
01:14:58,026 --> 01:14:59,357
That would be nice.

1098
01:15:05,968 --> 01:15:07,492
How is he?

1099
01:15:08,670 --> 01:15:10,570
Medium rare.

1100
01:15:10,672 --> 01:15:12,003
Another hour.

1101
01:15:18,747 --> 01:15:19,805
So...

1102
01:15:19,915 --> 01:15:22,145
what were you
doing here, Marcello?

1103
01:15:22,251 --> 01:15:24,947
I came to feed the chickens,
like a friend would.

1104
01:15:25,053 --> 01:15:27,954
Then I saw him.
Was a terrible shock.

1105
01:15:28,056 --> 01:15:30,388
Then why is he sitting there?

1106
01:15:30,492 --> 01:15:31,823
It was his favorite spot.

1107
01:15:31,927 --> 01:15:34,157
Think of it. He knows
his life is slipping away,

1108
01:15:34,263 --> 01:15:36,424
and this is the picture
he wants to take with him.

1109
01:15:36,532 --> 01:15:39,160
Ah, yesterday you said
he was halfway to Tahiti.

1110
01:15:39,268 --> 01:15:40,462
And the day before,

1111
01:15:40,569 --> 01:15:42,161
I told you he was wandering about,
dazed and confused.

1112
01:15:42,271 --> 01:15:44,171
And I was right.

1113
01:15:44,273 --> 01:15:46,138
What about the sock?

1114
01:15:47,609 --> 01:15:49,008
What about it?

1115
01:15:49,111 --> 01:15:50,510
Does it look like
the sock of a man

1116
01:15:50,612 --> 01:15:53,342
who's been wandering
around the countryside?

1117
01:15:53,448 --> 01:15:55,313
My friend is dead,
and you're worrying about...

1118
01:15:56,418 --> 01:15:58,716
the state of his socks?

1119
01:15:58,820 --> 01:16:01,015
Doctor, you're the expert.

1120
01:16:01,123 --> 01:16:04,115
In your professional opinion,
what time did he die?

1121
01:16:04,226 --> 01:16:05,625
I'd say...

1122
01:16:05,727 --> 01:16:07,786
a few hours ago.

1123
01:16:07,896 --> 01:16:09,955
I'd like to call an ambulance.

1124
01:16:10,065 --> 01:16:11,032
Very well.

1125
01:16:51,940 --> 01:16:54,500
- I won't be gone long.
- Where are you going?

1126
01:16:54,610 --> 01:16:57,238
Not to the hospital,
looking like that.

1127
01:17:34,483 --> 01:17:35,973
Roseanna.

1128
01:17:36,084 --> 01:17:38,143
May I come in?

1129
01:17:38,253 --> 01:17:39,618
Yes.

1130
01:17:47,262 --> 01:17:49,696
It wasn't easy for me
to come here.

1131
01:17:54,636 --> 01:17:58,094
This place hasn't changed
in 20 years.

1132
01:17:58,206 --> 01:18:01,004
There was never a woman
worth changing it for.

1133
01:18:13,522 --> 01:18:16,616
You could have been
the richest woman in Trevento,

1134
01:18:16,725 --> 01:18:19,057
and you chose a cyclist with a bar.

1135
01:18:19,161 --> 01:18:22,130
Virgilio,
we cannot argue fate.

1136
01:18:22,230 --> 01:18:24,494
Mine was Marcello.

1137
01:18:24,599 --> 01:18:28,126
And see how fate turns around.

1138
01:18:28,236 --> 01:18:30,136
He took the one thing I wanted,

1139
01:18:30,238 --> 01:18:31,603
and I have
the one thing he wants.

1140
01:18:31,707 --> 01:18:35,074
Then for the sake of the feelings
that you once had for me,

1141
01:18:35,177 --> 01:18:36,610
give it to him.

1142
01:18:38,747 --> 01:18:42,444
And will you give me back
20 years of happiness?

1143
01:18:43,552 --> 01:18:45,110
Virgilio,

1144
01:18:45,220 --> 01:18:47,654
I beg you,

1145
01:18:47,756 --> 01:18:49,747
let the land go.

1146
01:18:52,427 --> 01:18:54,258
All right.

1147
01:18:57,099 --> 01:19:00,159
But first
I want an admission,

1148
01:19:00,268 --> 01:19:03,499
an admission
that you made a mistake,

1149
01:19:03,605 --> 01:19:06,267
that when you turned me down,
it was not only an insult,

1150
01:19:06,374 --> 01:19:08,103
it was... stupid.

1151
01:19:08,210 --> 01:19:10,508
That you married a man
who had nothing 20 years ago

1152
01:19:10,612 --> 01:19:11,977
and has nothing now.

1153
01:19:12,080 --> 01:19:15,447
That if you married me,
you would have had...

1154
01:19:15,550 --> 01:19:17,108
everything.

1155
01:19:17,219 --> 01:19:20,620
That I could have provided you
with better doctors than he did,

1156
01:19:20,722 --> 01:19:23,122
and that your child
would still be alive.

1157
01:19:23,225 --> 01:19:24,624
Admit that.

1158
01:19:25,727 --> 01:19:27,854
Then you can have your land.

1159
01:19:30,465 --> 01:19:32,399
This is so sad.

1160
01:19:33,735 --> 01:19:35,965
You are so sad.

1161
01:19:37,072 --> 01:19:40,132
Look at this house
that you live in.

1162
01:19:40,242 --> 01:19:42,938
There is no soul.

1163
01:19:43,044 --> 01:19:45,137
There is no joy.

1164
01:19:45,247 --> 01:19:47,647
There is no peace.

1165
01:19:47,749 --> 01:19:52,413
My life with Marcello
has been filled with these things.

1166
01:19:56,191 --> 01:19:58,386
Step outside
of this opera you are living in.

1167
01:19:58,493 --> 01:20:00,518
It is not me
you are angry with.

1168
01:20:00,629 --> 01:20:01,857
It's you.

1169
01:20:30,225 --> 01:20:31,988
Amen.

1170
01:20:38,567 --> 01:20:40,125
He had a good life.

1171
01:20:40,235 --> 01:20:41,600
His chickens,

1172
01:20:41,703 --> 01:20:43,261
custom-made shirts,

1173
01:20:43,371 --> 01:20:44,633
and a mistress.

1174
01:20:44,739 --> 01:20:46,639
I'm not sure
she was a blessing.

1175
01:20:46,741 --> 01:20:48,641
She didn't send flowers.

1176
01:20:48,743 --> 01:20:51,143
Of course not.
His children were there.

1177
01:20:51,246 --> 01:20:52,611
He'll be missed.

1178
01:20:52,714 --> 01:20:53,681
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1179
01:20:53,782 --> 01:20:57,081
We need a fourth for cards.

1180
01:20:57,185 --> 01:20:59,585
You look beautiful
in black, Cecilia.

1181
01:20:59,688 --> 01:21:03,089
It's just as well. It's the color
this town wears most.

1182
01:21:03,191 --> 01:21:05,022
Strange way to die,
don't you think?

1183
01:21:05,126 --> 01:21:06,093
No.

1184
01:21:06,194 --> 01:21:09,095
Sergeant Baggio
had a word with me about it.

1185
01:21:09,197 --> 01:21:10,186
Why?

1186
01:21:10,298 --> 01:21:12,596
I'm a lawyer with some
criminal experience.

1187
01:21:12,701 --> 01:21:15,602
He thinks we don't know
the whole story.

1188
01:21:15,704 --> 01:21:18,104
- What does he think?
- Between ourselves?

1189
01:21:18,206 --> 01:21:20,640
He thinks the Mafia
are involved.

1190
01:21:38,727 --> 01:21:40,627
Roseanna, what's wrong?

1191
01:21:40,729 --> 01:21:44,927
Nothing. It's just
one of my bad days.

1192
01:21:45,033 --> 01:21:46,466
Do you need a pill?

1193
01:21:46,568 --> 01:21:48,468
I just took one.

1194
01:21:48,570 --> 01:21:50,128
Do you need the doctor?
He's in the bar.

1195
01:21:50,238 --> 01:21:52,035
No, no, no.

1196
01:21:52,240 --> 01:21:55,903
No, no, no, no, no, no.

1197
01:21:58,914 --> 01:22:01,382
Roseanna, I'm going to
take the rest of Rossi's money

1198
01:22:01,483 --> 01:22:03,007
and offer it to Capestro.

1199
01:22:04,185 --> 01:22:06,949
It's no use, Marcello.

1200
01:22:11,026 --> 01:22:14,325
Listen,
I have something to tell you.

1201
01:22:21,202 --> 01:22:23,602
You know that I adore you.

1202
01:22:24,706 --> 01:22:27,402
The first time I met you,

1203
01:22:27,509 --> 01:22:29,636
you touched my soul.

1204
01:22:32,347 --> 01:22:36,249
But there was a time
before I knew you.

1205
01:22:36,351 --> 01:22:38,444
Is it possible?

1206
01:22:38,553 --> 01:22:42,114
You know that I lived
on the Capestro estate

1207
01:22:42,223 --> 01:22:46,125
with my parents,
who were servants there.

1208
01:22:46,227 --> 01:22:48,286
I was 16

1209
01:22:48,396 --> 01:22:51,763
when Virgilio came back
from the university.

1210
01:22:52,867 --> 01:22:54,630
And he was...

1211
01:22:54,736 --> 01:22:56,636
he was very handsome,

1212
01:22:56,738 --> 01:23:01,573
with all the arrogance
of wealth and youth.

1213
01:23:01,676 --> 01:23:05,077
I don't think I'm going to like
what you're going to tell me.

1214
01:23:05,180 --> 01:23:07,614
No, You're not.

1215
01:23:08,717 --> 01:23:10,082
He seduced you.

1216
01:23:11,486 --> 01:23:13,113
Not exactly.

1217
01:23:16,024 --> 01:23:18,015
I'm sorry.

1218
01:23:18,126 --> 01:23:21,584
I'm sorry, Marcello.

1219
01:23:21,696 --> 01:23:23,596
I was very young,

1220
01:23:23,698 --> 01:23:27,600
and I was flattered
by the attention of such a man.

1221
01:23:27,702 --> 01:23:29,966
He asked me to marry him.

1222
01:23:31,072 --> 01:23:32,539
Why didn't you?

1223
01:23:35,210 --> 01:23:38,475
I met you.
It's that simple.

1224
01:23:41,216 --> 01:23:42,615
So, you see,

1225
01:23:42,717 --> 01:23:45,777
this is the anger
that he has in his heart for you,

1226
01:23:45,887 --> 01:23:48,481
and money cannot
make this go away.

1227
01:23:51,226 --> 01:23:54,662
You've done
everything you could.

1228
01:23:56,031 --> 01:23:58,329
You have to let go now.

1229
01:24:20,321 --> 01:24:21,583
Amen.

1230
01:24:43,545 --> 01:24:44,512
Capestro!

1231
01:24:49,017 --> 01:24:50,985
Half an acre.

1232
01:24:51,086 --> 01:24:53,020
That's all that was
ever asked of you.

1233
01:24:53,121 --> 01:24:54,679
Not only for my wife,

1234
01:24:54,789 --> 01:24:57,280
but for all
the people of Trevento

1235
01:24:57,392 --> 01:25:00,555
who wanted to be buried
where their ancestors were.

1236
01:25:00,662 --> 01:25:03,062
If you have business with me,

1237
01:25:03,164 --> 01:25:05,132
you come to me on a Monday

1238
01:25:05,233 --> 01:25:07,667
and you talk to my lawyer.

1239
01:25:07,769 --> 01:25:11,136
In front of God,
you're a sick man,

1240
01:25:11,239 --> 01:25:13,139
consumed with
jealousy and hatred

1241
01:25:13,241 --> 01:25:15,141
because of the woman
you couldn't have.

1242
01:25:15,243 --> 01:25:16,870
Please, stop this.

1243
01:25:16,978 --> 01:25:18,809
Stop this right now.

1244
01:25:18,913 --> 01:25:22,007
I would be buried
10,000 kilometers from my daughter

1245
01:25:22,117 --> 01:25:25,518
before I would take one thing
from the hand of this man.

1246
01:25:25,620 --> 01:25:27,485
If you were half of what you are

1247
01:25:27,589 --> 01:25:29,648
and he was twice what he is,

1248
01:25:29,757 --> 01:25:30,951
you would still be ten...

1249
01:25:32,060 --> 01:25:33,550
you would st...

1250
01:25:35,830 --> 01:25:38,663
you would still be
ten times the man he is!

1251
01:25:40,034 --> 01:25:41,399
Get the doctor! Quickly!

1252
01:25:41,503 --> 01:25:42,902
I'm here, Marcello!
I'm here.

1253
01:25:46,508 --> 01:25:47,475
Roseanna.

1254
01:25:48,510 --> 01:25:49,534
Roseanna.

1255
01:26:42,764 --> 01:26:48,168
I'm very sorry to tell you,
but Roseanna,

1256
01:26:48,269 --> 01:26:50,100
my wife,

1257
01:26:50,205 --> 01:26:52,173
my beloved,

1258
01:26:52,273 --> 01:26:56,607
the most wonderful woman
that ever lived,

1259
01:26:56,711 --> 01:26:58,611
has passed away

1260
01:27:00,715 --> 01:27:03,115
This is not the time for weeping,

1261
01:27:03,218 --> 01:27:05,618
it's a time for joy,

1262
01:27:05,720 --> 01:27:08,280
because she will be buried

1263
01:27:08,389 --> 01:27:11,688
in the last grave
of the cemetery with her...

1264
01:27:13,728 --> 01:27:15,696
Marcellina.

1265
01:27:17,232 --> 01:27:20,861
This she wanted more than life.

1266
01:27:20,969 --> 01:27:23,267
This God has granted her.

1267
01:27:25,740 --> 01:27:28,573
This makes me happy.

1268
01:29:19,020 --> 01:29:21,045
Roseanna has her dying wish.

1269
01:29:22,223 --> 01:29:24,623
I would have gone,

1270
01:29:24,726 --> 01:29:28,059
but I thought
they wouldn't want me.

1271
01:29:28,162 --> 01:29:30,562
You're probably right.

1272
01:29:32,734 --> 01:29:35,635
I want you to draw up papers

1273
01:29:35,737 --> 01:29:38,137
transferring the necessary land

1274
01:29:38,239 --> 01:29:40,969
from my estate to the church.

1275
01:29:41,075 --> 01:29:43,009
A deed of gift.

1276
01:29:43,111 --> 01:29:47,639
Maybe now you'll
hate that family less.

1277
01:29:47,749 --> 01:29:51,150
I also want you to know
I'm in love with Cecilia...

1278
01:29:51,252 --> 01:29:53,652
and I intend to ask her
to marry me.

1279
01:29:56,557 --> 01:29:57,524
Antonio...

1280
01:30:00,528 --> 01:30:02,621
I loved her.

1281
01:30:04,699 --> 01:30:07,167
It ruined my life.

1282
01:31:25,480 --> 01:31:27,072
Hey, Cecilia!

1283
01:31:29,150 --> 01:31:31,015
Hey, Cecilia!

1284
01:31:32,119 --> 01:31:33,279
Cecilia!

1285
01:31:38,292 --> 01:31:40,260
- Where is everybody?
- Gone.

1286
01:31:40,361 --> 01:31:41,555
Well, gone where?

1287
01:31:41,662 --> 01:31:44,130
Marcello wanted to get away.

1288
01:31:44,232 --> 01:31:47,395
He has a cousin in Como.
Who can blame him?

1289
01:31:47,502 --> 01:31:50,471
- And Cecilia?
- She took him to the station.

1290
01:31:50,571 --> 01:31:52,095
I think she is going with him.

1291
01:31:53,608 --> 01:31:56,042
Why not?
It was her sister's wish.

1292
01:32:23,704 --> 01:32:25,137
Cecilia!

1293
01:32:29,243 --> 01:32:31,871
- Antonio.
- Marcello, forgive me.

1294
01:32:31,979 --> 01:32:33,640
Is this true?
Is she going with you?

1295
01:32:33,748 --> 01:32:35,807
What is this all about, Antonio?

1296
01:32:35,917 --> 01:32:37,111
You could at least
have said good-bye!

1297
01:32:37,218 --> 01:32:39,243
There were so many things
I wanted to say to you,

1298
01:32:39,353 --> 01:32:42,117
and I waited, out of respect,
until your sister had passed on.

1299
01:32:42,223 --> 01:32:44,623
Why don't you put this in a letter?

1300
01:32:44,725 --> 01:32:46,352
You're doing this out of duty!

1301
01:32:46,460 --> 01:32:47,620
You don't love each other!

1302
01:32:47,728 --> 01:32:50,356
And I do love you, Cecilia.
I really do.

1303
01:32:53,901 --> 01:32:56,267
You are wrong, Antonio.

1304
01:32:57,772 --> 01:33:00,639
We love each other
very much.

1305
01:33:00,741 --> 01:33:02,936
Roseanna, I mean...
what's going on?

1306
01:33:03,044 --> 01:33:04,944
<i>Ay yi! We were
almost on the train!</i>

1307
01:33:05,046 --> 01:33:06,809
I have my grave reserved for me,

1308
01:33:06,914 --> 01:33:09,178
but it can wait
until I am ready for it.

1309
01:33:09,283 --> 01:33:12,650
In the meantime, Marcello
and I have some living to do.

1310
01:33:16,324 --> 01:33:18,485
And Cecilia?
I mean, where is she?

1311
01:33:18,593 --> 01:33:21,494
Keeping out of the way.
You can see her tonight.

1312
01:33:21,596 --> 01:33:23,029
It's our secret,

1313
01:33:23,130 --> 01:33:25,894
and if you care
about Cecilia, be part of it.

1314
01:33:34,475 --> 01:33:36,636
Have a good life, huh?

1315
01:33:41,582 --> 01:33:42,549
Marcello.

1316
01:33:58,232 --> 01:33:59,631
Menu, sir?

1317
01:33:59,734 --> 01:34:02,703
No, thank you. We'll be dining
on the plane to New York.

1318
01:34:04,705 --> 01:34:06,935
You say that as if
you do this all the time,

1319
01:34:07,041 --> 01:34:09,407
and you've never been
on a plane in your life.

1320
01:34:14,715 --> 01:34:17,240
- We did it!
- Yes!

1321
01:34:20,221 --> 01:34:23,452
But the first thing we have to do
when we go to New York

1322
01:34:23,557 --> 01:34:27,118
is find a church and confess
to the priest for being so wicked.

1323
01:34:27,228 --> 01:34:28,627
Have we been so wicked?

1324
01:34:28,729 --> 01:34:31,630
Of course, or else
it wouldn't feel so good.

1325
01:34:34,235 --> 01:34:36,135
Tell me something...

1326
01:34:36,237 --> 01:34:39,638
is the mayor of New York
still Italian?

1327
01:34:39,740 --> 01:34:42,402
Why would anybody want
to stop being Italian?

